            <thetext>qx.ui.virtual.core.Axis allows to set custom item sizes, but higher than 0.

Mind you want to collapse one or more items in a virtual meaning. Selection of virtual widgets are base on a coordination system (row and column indexes). If we would remove some items because of collapsing, the previous added selection coordinates would be wrong. Therefor I recommend to add spacer items instead of widgets and set the height of an axis item to 0.

So multiple selection like selection by range is possible even widgets are collapsed between to visible widget.

Currently the smallest height of an axis item is 1px. This results on a unwanted gap, even if more axis items were collapsed.</thetext>
